INSERT  IGNORE INTO `private_message` (`id`, `thread`, `sender`, `receiver`, `subject`, `body`, `is_rich`, `is_read`, `is_replied`, `is_forwarded`, `is_marked`, `is_deleted`, `created_at`) VALUES (1,'fec47bef10380da0a5c66a96e193de34',52,5,'RE: featured collector ?','Sure, that would be awesome!  I won\'t get a chance to upload more items until tomorrow tho.',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-06-19 03:09:20'),(2,'d4776e976b9f60f1390ee91461b2a565',52,5,'RE: You\'ve been featured','Thanks Martin!<br /><br />\nI have many more things to upload - I\'ll be adding pictures a little bit at a time.  The mass upload feature really does make it easy!  I like action figures and I enjoy reading the blog posts on CQ about them, but the only ones I collect are Jurassic Park - go figure!  I\'ll post pictures of them eventually!',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-06-19 23:00:31'),(3,'87f0722ca94f51ae802358976d9d2f61',52,5,'trouble uploading','Hi Martin,<br /><br />\nI just wanted to let you know that I have been having trouble uploading images.  It seems to get stuck uploading the first image.  The green bar just keeps going.  I think I am uploading the right format because its the same as all the other pics I\'ve uploaded.<br /><br />\nJust wanted to let you know incase there\'s a problem.<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-06-27 01:21:46'),(4,'e86a7dddb2097b3aef38af8bfa247502',52,5,'RE: batch upload should work now','Ok - I just tried it and it worked - thanks!<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-06-27 22:57:06'),(5,'e86a7dddb2097b3aef38af8bfa247502',52,5,'RE: RE: RE: batch upload should work now','Cool - sorry about the long name.<br /><br />\nI\'m really enjoying the site<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-06-27 23:15:05'),(6,'b4e7f470049ed3df51f25726d2577798',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: batch upload','Would I kid a techie?! lol<br /><br />\nI switched to it because the number of projects I have ongoing was too much for Windows to handle and I kept crashing. ;)  I love it, and adore Firefox, until it comes to media.  They need to get to work on improving it for the few of us (we are growing in numbers and plan on taking over the Internet lol)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-02 20:15:45'),(7,'b4e7f470049ed3df51f25726d2577798',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: batch upload','Sorry it took so long for a reply -- I had to make dinner for the kids (and then, true hoarders and historians that we are, we watched not only Antiques Roadshow but my favorite, History Detectives *wink*)<br /><br />\nI took a look at your screen shot -- but must confess, no matter what the cost, that I am no programmer. (Derek is tho so that strange collection of stuff looks familiar if unintelligible lol).  I know few others who use linux, but honestly, to not have things crash all the time is a dream.  (Well, unless you would happen to go to MySpace or someother imbeded nightmare of a page, then firefox will die -- but all my documents and assignments are fine.)<br /><br />\nI should clarify, I can listen to mp3s and watch video etc if I save it and watch it, and youtube is dandy.  But imbedded stuff :ouch:  The built in media players are too \'old\' and not accepted at too many sites -- and when you try to set your media to say RealPlayer, it doesn\'t believe you lol and tries to load the crud anyway.<br /><br />\nI look forward to the bulk uploader for we (few) linux folks.  (And open source to upgrade us to better media in general.)  Cuz I\'d rather limp along as needed than have my pc crash and lose my writing/work.  ;)<br /><br />\nAre you still working?!',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-02 22:15:42'),(8,'31afd4f2462c407240958b7154610dcb',59,5,'RE: RE: You Know...','Oh, well, then I am glad to have shown you a bug before this joint gets HUGE :p',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-07-03 23:27:12'),(9,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: what do u think of these','Wowza!  Some of those are stunning!<br /><br />\nOK, back to your question... I think, based on talks on the phone, she\'s rather thinking along these lines:<br /><br />\nNo nudity at all (unless \'classic art\' or \'true art\' by a \'real artist\' which is going to be difficult to define no matter how you slice it as currently even museums are caving to cries of \"that\'s porn!\")<br /><br />\nOr, nude works can be shown with those areas blacked/blocked out (which rather defeats/destroys the collection, IMO).<br /><br />\nThough she did discuss a flag system where photos/images could be marked as \'offensive\' by members -- which would then send a notice to you all, and you\'d decide the object\'s merits.  If \'real art\' then it would be flagged \'mature\' or \'risque\' and a member would have to click \'ok, I want to view it anyway\' and then see it (without the blacked/boxed stuff).  But as that doesn\'t exist yet...<br /><br />\nThis is why I\'m not going to try my vintage postcards (even the humor ones), but rather wait for the adult site.  It\'s too confusing and there\'s no policy on it all.  Ambiguity = Frustration, so I will pass ;)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 00:36:45'),(10,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','A few questions...<br /><br />\nWill you be up for awhile if I do?<br /><br />\nAnd what\'s the official guideline on this \'mature\' content?  I\'ve posted it at \'my dirty collectibles blog\' and if some of them come over I don\'t want to confuse them with what is or isn\'t allowed...<br /><br />\nWill it work with linux? :p',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 00:54:24'),(11,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','Is she back from vacation?   I thought I saw her on yesterday too, but figured that was just the \'office\' account checking for her or something...<br /><br />\nI\'ll see what I can do with the stuff here.  Photos and whatnot ;)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 01:23:19'),(12,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','the test is live ;)  I messaged you from there too (part of the 3 letter name test lol)<br /><br />\nI am interested in the results of this test -- I have varying degrees of offensive there ;)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 03:01:51'),(13,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','So now what?  We wait for Liz to say something?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 03:06:51'),(14,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','There are two of those -- and if she yelps, remind her that these items are sold on eBay.  In fact, racist Black Americana is a huge market...  Will people hate it? Yeah, but like I wrote, it\'s history.  Like Nazi stuff.  It was real, and therefore hugely collected by Whoopie Goldberg and others.<br /><br />\nI expect the Hindu one to be most offensive (the \'snake\' and all). ;)<br /><br />\nMost popular?  Perhaps, but also the largest headache ;)  See the \'mature\' warning works on collections, not items.  So if you use the item tags, say for \'risque,\' then bam!  Offended.  Maybe the flag should do some sort of masking until they click \'ok to see\' and then the item images show...<br /><br />\nI\'m not selling the nutcracker?  Is it marked that way?!  (They are rather common on ebay -- not hundreds of them, but enough to find one or 6 lol)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 03:15:40'),(15,'79146774be50423136256de1f84cbc6d',59,5,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: what do u think of these','Well, your idea works for \'risque\' but not for \'vintage\' or \'postcards\' etc.  So the risk is still there...<br /><br />\nWhat ebay and other sites do is have items \'marked\' or \'flagged\' and then a person has to say \'ok\' to see things flagged.  I don\'t know a thing about programming it...<br /><br />\nSo the complete other site, for adult stuff might be easier.  However, as a collector of racist stuff, I wouldn\'t look there for it.  So the blackface cards wouldn\'t be looked for there.<br /><br />\nAs for ebay and racist stuff:<br /><br />\nhttp://search.ebay.com/search/search.dll?from=R40&amp;_trksid=m37&amp;satitle=blackface&amp;category0=<br /><br />\nhttp://collectibles.listings.ebay.com/Cultures-Ethnicities_Black-Americana_W0QQfclZ3QQfromZR11QQsacatZ29457QQsocmdZListingItemList<br /><br />\nhttp://collectibles.search.ebay.com/racist_Black-Americana_W0QQcatrefZC6QQcoactionZcompareQQcoentrypageZsearchQQcopagenumZ1QQfclZ3QQfgtpZQQfposZ58102QQfromZR2QQfsooZ2QQfsopZ2QQftrtZ1QQftrvZ1QQlopgZQQsabfmtsZ1QQsacatZ29457QQsadisZ200QQsaobfmtsZinsifQQsaprchiZQQsaprcloZQQsargnZQ2d1QQsaslcZ2QQsbrftogZ1QQsofocusZbs<br /><br />\nBe sure to look at the store listings (at the bottom too)<br /><br />\nThis took all of 3 minutes lol',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-04 03:38:03'),(16,'0166782cd379f32d9c1b3a12cdd3bf00',59,5,'RE: collection title','Oh I know you just hate me :p<br /><br />\nSure it\'s not the dots (...) cuz other titles were longer (I think)?<br /><br />\nHas Liz said anything about the naughty collections yet?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-05 12:07:50'),(17,'06b0da492329e5018c65d1789b0ffbbb',59,5,'Bug Found','FYI, when you look at person\'s profile and use the text link at the right to make them a buddy, you get an error message telling you they already are a buddy.  So folks have to use the general collectors page and use the make a buddy icon (next to message icon) in order to really make a connection.<br /><br />\nI noticed this when I was SPS but just thought it was a one-time glitch, but it happened again today.',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-08 18:28:00'),(18,'c7775b9f90952caaca60dbaf52c3aab8',59,75,'HI & Nice To See You Here!','Hi again :)<br /><br />\nJust letting you know that if you have any questions, let me know &amp; I\'d be glad to help. :)<br /><br />\nDeanna',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-07-08 19:27:32'),(19,'4066dd678f18af328be0af77eaabd27d',52,6,'RE: Package to Send','Wow Liz,  Thank you so much!  I have really been enjoying the site - I appreciate the work you and your team have put into it!  You can reach me at:<br /><br />\nBrian Platt<br /><br />\n2302 E. 27th Terrace<br /><br />\nLawrence, KS 66046<br /><br />\nI wish you continued success with Collectors\' Quest!<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-07-31 21:15:51'),(20,'17f8ae2c4b7dd1d78abcbe91a883394b',12,6,'RE: Display Issues on Site','Evening!<br /><br />\nI\'m still trying to figure out what\'s wrong - but it\'s likely it\'s just some quirk with my computer. I\'m not having trouble with any other site at all, but I\'ll send over a screenshot of how it looks. I\'m using the most recent version of Firefox on a Mac running OSX.<br /><br />\nEverything looks great except for the very first welcome screen, where all of the display elements are gone and the three featured collections are running down the lefthand side of the page. I\'ll send an image to your eMail in a moment.<br /><br />\ncollin',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-08-04 01:37:46'),(21,'f99e51463bff6acefa35fc5049757220',52,142,'RE: A contest for collectors','Lisa,<br /><br />\nThank you for letting me know about this contest - it sounds cool!  I am certainly obsessed - everybody around here knows me as the guy who collects dinosaurs.  Some of the pictures on CollectorsQuest here are from my old room at my parent\'s house - so that won\'t qualify.  But I do have a pretty large collection with me now - I live in a \"town home\", but I am renting it - does that qualify?<br /><br />\nThanks,<br /><br />\nBrian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-08-22 11:14:36'),(22,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'Records','Hi!<br /><br />\nDo you have an online store or website?  If so, please put the url in your profile so that I and others may find \'you\' there :)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 00:22:14'),(23,'5b088050116f020afa8f1b0917a404d7',59,5,'Picky & Naggin\'','Nope, it\'s not a band -- it\'s me with some CQ community notes ;)<br /><br />\nA) I got a message her in the CQ community and I noticed a boo-boo of the oversight variety.  At the top of the message, where it says the name of who the message is from, why isn\'t that a link to the member\'s profile?  I sent a note to a member asking a question.  She replied, but there wasn\'t a super easy way to find her profile.  Sure, I may add her as a buddy, but right now I had to search for her and even if she was a buddy, why should I have to hunt for her?  It seems to me that I should just be able to click her name at the to of the message and get her profile, right?<br /><br />\nB) The my buddies page (http://www.collectorsquest.com/community/buddies.html) should have something in the right column there... Maybe a way to see which of my buddies are online?  (Or maybe all profiles should have an icon for \'online now\'?)  Anyway, there\'s wasted space on that page and I don\'t believe in wasting space ;)<br /><br />\nHope all is well.  I\'ll send a copy of this to Liz too.<br /><br />\nD',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:04:18'),(24,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: Records','Hi Heather,<br /><br />\nI\'m one of the writers for Collectors\' Quest, Deanna Dahlsad.  (So is my husband, Derek.)  We also have our own online stores and a silly pop culture/collecting blog (which is why Collectors\' Quest liked us, I guess lol)<br /><br />\nSince Hubby and I play our records and keep darn near everything, we sell very few records. ;)<br /><br />\nBe sure to put your real store name etc in your profile so that others can find you.  As this community grows, the selling/trading will take off more too.  (As trendy as it sounds, we\'re still in Beta I guess, with lots more to come.)<br /><br />\nAnd I guess, while I am babbling, I\'m always interested in interviewing for articles here at CQ... Interested?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:11:50'),(25,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'M & M\'s and You','Howdy!<br /><br />\nI write for Collectors\' Quest (http://www.collectorsquest.com/blog/index.php?author=3), and I\'d love, love, LOVE to interview you!  Are you interested?<br /><br />\nPopTart aka Deanna Dahlsad',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-23 23:28:30'),(26,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'RE: RE: M & M\'s and You','Hi Karen,<br /><br />\nEmail or this here messaging is fine for me, if that works for you...<br /><br />\nI\'ve taken the liberty of including some starter questions -- if you\'d prefer to do this via the phone, just let me know :)<br /><br />\nWhen did you begin collecting M&amp;M items?  Why?<br /><br />\nHow many items in your collection?<br /><br />\nWhat\'s the most extreme you\'ve gone for any item?  (distance travelled, most paid etc.)<br /><br />\nDo you collect anything else?<br /><br />\nWhat\'s a \'holy grail\' item you still seek?<br /><br />\nTell me more about this artist &amp; the work...  What\'s the story behind it.  How did they find you?  What\'s the purpose of the art to be?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-24 02:25:28'),(27,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: RE: RE: Records','Hello Heather,<br /><br />\nHere are some starter questions -- I\'ve taken the liberty to start here, but if you\'d prefer to do this via the phone, just let me know :)<br /><br />\nWhen did you begin collecting records?  Why?<br /><br />\nHow many items in your collection?<br /><br />\nWhat\'s the most extreme you\'ve gone for any item?  (distance travelled, most paid etc.)<br /><br />\nDo you collect anything else?<br /><br />\nWhat\'s a \'holy grail\' item you still seek?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-24 02:27:26'),(28,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'RE: RE: RE: RE: M & M\'s and You','Hi Karen,<br /><br />\nIt will be published here, at CQ!  (Did I not mention that?!)<br /><br />\nhttp://www.collectorsquest.com<br /><br />\nSorry for any confusion :)',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-09-25 13:10:54'),(29,'cccb6630bdf4df027b4ae35747a9bb18',59,154,'RE: RE: RE: RE: M & M\'s and You','Just a few more questions...<br /><br />\nCan you tell me more about the 20/20 episode? What was it about and why were you on it?<br /><br />\nYou\'ve been on several news programs -- for the same reason(s)?<br /><br />\nHow long did it take for you to make the costume?  (And did it cost more than you won?)<br /><br />\nSince you\'ve got such a huge collection, how has that changed your collecting?<br /><br />\nEsp in terms of gifts... In the beginning it must have been easy for anyone to grab an M&amp;M item to surprise &amp; delight you, but now... Well, are folks put off of supporting your collection because there\'s so little you don\'t already have?<br /><br />\nIt\'s hard to imagine anyone challenging you to a collection contest lol  Who won the Hard Rock item contest, you or your husband?<br /><br />\nDoes your husband collect anything (else)?<br /><br />\nPlease rank in order (from highest to lowest), the following attributes/skills as far as they pertain to your collection success:<br /><br />\nPassion<br /><br />\nInsanity<br /><br />\nThrifty<br /><br />\nOrganized<br /><br />\nA sense of humor<br /><br />\nOther (please list)<br /><br />\nIf you had to describe which attribute has helped you as a collector the most -- which one is most \'needed\' to be a collector -- which would it be?<br /><br />\nAnd, of course, I have to ask you, do you like the candies themselves? ;)<br /><br />\nHow would you like to be known?  As your user ID, as Karen, by your full name?  (And if the latter, please tell me your full name.)<br /><br />\nCan you email me the photo from your profile here (the one of you in your costume)?  Also, any images, including if you made yourself an M&amp;M on the website, I\'d be happy to include them :)<br /><br />\nYou can email it/them to me at: Deanna@collectorsquest.com<br /><br />\nAlong with your profile here, is there anything I should link to?  (Do you have a blog or website etc.)<br /><br />\nThanks -- Oh, and in your profile, you say your costume has a coin \'slut\' -- which is very funny :P  But I thought maybe you\'d like to know lol<br /><br />\nD',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-10-04 04:30:27'),(30,'38095e22dffb3797077bd908b0d0bc15',59,154,'Interview Questions','Did you get the second set of interview questions?',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-10-10 13:59:24'),(31,'bba983a7f18f817a383b02f4080616b7',59,5,'why can\'t I open my sent messages?','I was trying to find the interview questions I sent, but cannot open messages I sent...  Is this a new bug?  Either way, it is a problem to see a list of messages but not be able to open them...',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-10-10 14:02:59'),(32,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: RE: RE: Records','Did you get the questions I sent?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-10-10 14:04:11'),(33,'2d41f65bd3820b0c78e5e4a30c34f8a2',59,143,'RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: RE: Records','There seems to be a bug here, and I cannot open the messages sent??  I\'ve asked tech to look at it, but for now I cannot resend it... Is it possible to call you?',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-10-10 22:44:57'),(34,'60f460d03946bf9862ea775d8e20acbf',59,6,'posession obsession','I just emailed you -- I hope you get it before I leave :)',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-10-18 00:15:13'),(35,'4066dd678f18af328be0af77eaabd27d',52,6,'RE: RE: RE: Package to Send','Hi Liz,<br /><br />\nThank you so much for the package of dinosaurs!  You were right - I did not have any of those things in my collection before!  I especially like the big Stegosaurus puppet - I might be able to use it when I talk to schoolgroups about dinosaurs (I\'m going for my PhD in geology/paleontology and I\'m into public education).  And I have wanted that Dinopix book since I first saw some of the art a few years ago!<br /><br />\nI\'m really enjoying the site - I check it out almost every day - I like to read the blogs and look at other people\'s collections.  I have already had two dinosaur collectors contact me to talk dinos because they found my profile on CQ!<br /><br />\nThank you again!<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-10-25 19:30:12'),(36,'8d67bb4f36918e9f52d5118c79d1a2c2',12,188,'RE: Marvel 3age','Ahoy!<br /><br />\nI wish I could tell you, but I have NO record. I know that I imported one series from Japan, and one from the UK - nothing I could find in the US at all. All Googled to a million pages in my exhaustive search.<br /><br />\nGood luck. :)<br /><br />\nc david',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-11-05 19:20:52'),(37,'587c96e528314b04f9fceb7853ffa63b',59,154,'Interview','Hi there :)<br /><br />\nI did post what I could of the interview... The link is here:<br /><br />\nhttp://www.collectorsquest.com/blog/2007/11/26/an-interview-with-a-mm-collector/<br /><br />\nI did try to contact you with a few other questions, but when I didn\'t hear from you I went with what we had.  Should you see any errors, please let me know!<br /><br />\nThanks much, and please keep adding photos of your collections!<br /><br />\nDeanna',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-11-26 00:39:40'),(38,'bba983a7f18f817a383b02f4080616b7',59,5,'RE: RE: why can\'t I open my sent messages?','Still cannot open them...',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-11-26 00:40:12'),(39,'9d55b2238d9b7771ebf80e4edf878481',52,200,'RE: Your Dino Collection','Hi Jac,<br /><br />\nThank you for your kind message.  I\'m glad you enjoyed looking through my collection photos.  Dinosaur collectibles aren\'t very common, which makes hunting for them even more fun.  I have many more things than what I have posted on Collectors Quest so far.  I do have some Dinosaurs Attack cards - but I don\'t have a complete set.  I\'m not sure if I have the other wax pack wrapper - but thank you for letting me know about it.  I will have to take a look and see if I have it.<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-11-30 11:56:29'),(40,'5f8ac725cf4a1fb2043f9af51fac80b2',59,5,'can\'t login to get mail!','I\'ve tried several times, but no luck -- and I have 2 interviews going, so it\'s rather important...<br /><br />\nHelp!',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-12-13 18:28:26'),(41,'9d55b2238d9b7771ebf80e4edf878481',52,200,'RE: RE: RE: Your Dino Collection','Hi John,<br /><br />\nThank you for all the info.  I only have Egg Stealers and Earth Shakers from Dinosaurs A Celebration - you can see it in my dinosaur comic book page here - I didn\'t know what the first issue was called so thank you for that - now I can look for it.<br /><br />\nI was not familiar with Wacko-saurs until you told me - I looked them up and now that I see them I remember I had a folder in elementary school with the exact same artwork on it!  I think I still have the folder, but its in 2 pieces from use.<br /><br />\nI didn\'t know there were comics of the Dinosaurs Attack cards - if you know of some web pages I can look at that would be great.  I often buy a comic book because there\'s a dinosaur on the cover - I love the artwork in comics - my wife gets mad at me because she used to collect X-Men comics and she thinks a comic\'s value is in the story, not the art.<br /><br />\nI would really appreciate the Dinosaurs Attack wrapper/pack you offered - I would be happy to send a S.A.S.E. if you send me your address.  Thank you!<br /><br />\nI think the book was The Shy Stegosaurus of Cricket Creek - I never read it, but I have a book called The Shy Stegosaurus of Indian Creek, which I think is the sequel - you can see it here in my dinosaur books collection.<br /><br />\nThere have been a lot of dinosaur finds lately - did you see the dinosaur mummy special on the National Geographic channel the other day?  I missed it :( Hopefully they will replay it.<br /><br />\nThanks again!<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2007-12-14 10:15:48'),(42,'5f8ac725cf4a1fb2043f9af51fac80b2',59,5,'RE: RE: can\'t login to get mail!','I don\'t have/didn\'t login into 2 accounts.<br /><br />\nAnd while it is working now, I didn\'t get mail sent to me on the 14th until later.  There must have been some sort of mail server hiccup...<br /><br />\nAgain, it\'s all working now.  (Just makes me really nervous when I\'ve got interviews going etc. because I\'d have to start them all over again &amp;/or risk losing contact.)',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2007-12-17 14:33:14'),(43,'10dc6763e3806be50f7cc5e19c9049a4',52,200,'RE: Reply to 12-14-07 message','Hi John,<br /><br />\nThank you for resending your email.  I actually did receive your first one, but I had a lot going on around the holidays so I was unable to get back to you.  Thank you for the information and the article.  Short-necked plesiosaurs are cool - the well known one from Kansas is Dolichorhynchops.  I think its in the Sea Monsters 3D imax film (which I still have not seen).  I will get the envelope in the mail soon!<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2008-01-23 13:12:14'),(44,'d49aa355e9636d34f840128790373dba',52,200,'RE: S.A.S.E.','Hi John,<br /><br />\nI received the envelope you sent back to me and I was pleasantly surprised with its contents!  I really really appreciate you sending me all that stuff.  I was not expecting all 3 packs of Dinosaurs Attack cards!  And the Wacko saurs stickers are awesome - I never had any - but the artwork is exactly the same as the folder I had when I was a kid - I will have to look for it the next time I am at my parents\' house.  Most of my collection is still in my old bedroom at my parents\' house in New Jersey - I have some D.A. cards there, but not many - I never had a whole set.  I looked through the 4 packs I have here in Kansas that I bought at a collectible show, but none of them had the Ankylosaurus in them.  And I\'m pretty sure I don\'t have that sticker in NJ either - sorry - I would send it to you if I had it.  I can keep an eye out for it for you.  I go to antique shops/estate sales/auctions/yard sales often so I can look for stuff for you if there is anything you collect.<br /><br />\nI only have a couple Flintstones things, but I would like to get more - mainly the Marx toys from the 60s.<br /><br />\nThe movie clip was fun to make - I figures it was worth embarrassing myself to try and win $20,000 - didn\'t win anything tho - oh well.  I borrowed a camcorder from my friend and filmed the clips.  Then I uploaded them to my Mac with the cable that came with the camcorder and edited them in iMovie - its pretty easy to get the hang of.  Let me know if you have any other questions about it.<br /><br />\nThanks again for everything - and nice stamps! (I\'m sorry if I didn\'t provide enough postage)  Did you stock up on those in 1989?  John Gurche is my favorite paleoartist.  When the stamps came out I got a free t-shirt from the post office with pictures of the stamps on it - I\'m not sure if I have a picture of it on this website or not.<br /><br />\n-Brian',0,1,0,0,0,0,'2008-02-08 20:46:19'),(45,'54128c61dd47d58aeed1ee0aaca23884',59,114,'Questions for Collectors','Hi,<br /><br />\nThis is Deanna Dahlsad from CollectorsQuest.com (you may know me better as Pop Tart from<br /><br />\nKitschy-Kitschy-Coo.com) and I\'m writing you today as I have already interviewed you, am<br /><br />\ninterviewing you -- or have been dying to ;)<br /><br />\nI\'m working on several of those continuing \'list\' pieces for Collectors Quest, and I\'d<br /><br />\nlike a quote (or a dozen!) from you.<br /><br />\nAs always, I will credit you with a one sentence bio, including a link to your website,<br /><br />\ncolumn, or blog (or other contact info). So be sure to include:<br /><br />\n* Your name as you wish to be made public<br /><br />\n* One or two sentences regarding you and your collection. (Ex. Jane Doe is an avid<br /><br />\ncollector of pens, bananas and is the mother of three.  She has no time to dust.)<br /><br />\n* Your URL &amp;/or contact info<br /><br />\n* If you have a profile at the CQ community, please provide that as well (this will be<br /><br />\nincluded in addition to your own personal URL)<br /><br />\nFeel free to pass this email along to collectors you know who would be interested.<br /><br />\nSpeedy replies are appreciated!  (Late replies may still be used -- and interesting<br /><br />\nreplies may lead to more interesting individual articles too.)<br /><br />\nIf you have any questions, please ask :)<br /><br />\nI thank you in advance,<br /><br />\nDeanna Dahlsad<br /><br />\nhttp://www.collectorsquest.com/<br /><br />\nPlease answer any/all of the questions you feel comfortable replying to:<br /><br />\n1)  What two characteristics or personal traits you feel are essential to being a<br /><br />\ncollector?<br /><br />\n2)  What do you collect -- and what is the most common reply you hear when you tell<br /><br />\npeople about your collection?  (Yes, blank stares and laughs are acceptable replies!)<br /><br />\n3)  As a collector, what is one thing you cannot live without?  (Not the objects/items<br /><br />\nthemselves, but other things related to collecting, such as \'space\', \'acid free paper\',<br /><br />\n\'eBay\' etc.)<br /><br />\n4)  What is the \'crown jewel\' of your collection?  Please include a photo, a description<br /><br />\nof the collection, a description of the item, and an explanation of why it\'s the crown<br /><br />\njewel in your collection.<br /><br />\n5) What \'holy grail\' are you currently seeking for your collection?  Please name/describe<br /><br />\nit, how you know of it, a description of the collection, a description of the item, and<br /><br />\nan explanation of why you need it in your collection.<br /><br />\n6) How many hours a week do you think you spend collecting?  This includes, but is not<br /><br />\nlimited to: shopping for items to purchase, admiring or talking about your collection,<br /><br />\nblogging/writing about your collection, attending shows/events, researching, dusting.<br /><br />\nFeel free to give breakdowns &amp;/or rationalizations if you\'d like.<br /><br />\n7) My belief is that \'3 or more of something makes a collection\'... What is your<br /><br />\ndefinition of a collection?<br /><br />\n8) Of the choices below, how do you classify yourself as a collector?<br /><br />\na) \'just\' a collector<br /><br />\nb) a collector/historian<br /><br />\nc) obsessed<br /><br />\nd) addicted<br /><br />\ne) a hoarder in general<br /><br />\nf) other or combination (please list)<br /><br />\nAnd now, state why!<br /><br />\n9) How many times a year do you visit museums &amp;/or other public displays (shrines)<br /><br />\ndedicated to your area of collecting?<br /><br />\n10) We\'ve all heard that eBay killed the mom &amp; pop antiques store/mall... Do you agree?<br /><br />\nDisagree?  And please state your reasoning.<br /><br />\n11) We all have our usual collector haunts online (websites, communities, blogs etc.),<br /><br />\nplaces we regularly read &amp;/or \'talk\' at.  Please list your top three -- include link/url<br /><br />\nplease!<br /><br />\n13) If you sell as well as collect, which came first, the selling or the collecting?<br /><br />\n14) If you sell as well as collect, please describe your criteria for selling vs.<br /><br />\nkeeping.  Is it difficult to make such decisions?<br /><br />\n15) We all love our collections, but how much... If you were stranded on a deserted<br /><br />\nisland, would you selfishly want your items with you, or would you prefer they were<br /><br />\nsafely protected back at home?  Feel free to name specific items which may differ.  For<br /><br />\nexample, you\'d like it all safe at home except for three GI Joes to play with; or you\'d<br /><br />\ntake it all with you, except for one rare item which should remain protected elsewhere.<br /><br />\n16) The rumor is that we \'can\'t take it with us\'... I know, I know; that\'s not my version<br /><br />\nof heaven either.  :sigh:  But, have you made preparations for the \'here after\' and made<br /><br />\nplans for your collection which will remain here after you\'ve gone?  Please explain.<br /><br />\n17) Collectors are often called \'crazy\' or otherwise told, \"You should be<br /><br />\ninstitutionalized,\" but let\'s stick to the objects themselves...<br /><br />\nHave you ever had a public display of your collection?  (Yard/garage sales do not count!<br /><br />\nlol)  If \'yes\', please give details such as what the collection is, when &amp; where it was<br /><br />\nshown, and who initiated the show (you or the institution/space).<br /><br />\n18) Related to the above, would you ever consider leaving your collection(s) to a museum<br /><br />\nor other institution?  Why or why not?<br /><br />\n19) Did you ever get an item for your collection so cheaply that you felt like a thief?<br /><br />\nEver stumble into such a great find that your fingers shook when you picked it up? Please<br /><br />\ninclude a photo, a description of the item, and your story of such a find.<br /><br />\n20) Do you have collecting \'bibles\'? (Price guides, reference books, magazines etc.) If<br /><br />\nso, please list your favorite three -- with a line about the importance/favor of each. If<br /><br />\nnot, why not?<br /><br />\n21) For those that live with others, do other members of your household collect? If<br /><br />\n\'yes\', what do they collect?  And does having multiple collectors in one home cause<br /><br />\nconflicts?  If \'no\', are they supportive (enablers) or do they mock your collecting<br /><br />\nhabits?<br /><br />\n22) What is the most \'over the top\' item in your collection?  (\'Over the top\' could be an<br /><br />\nitem you paid the most for, is the most mocked by others, an item you went to great<br /><br />\nlengths to get, was once greatly desired by you but now seems silly, or, somehow, is<br /><br />\notherwise outrageous or has an outrageous story behind it.)  Please include a photo, a<br /><br />\ndescription of the collection, a description of the item, and an explanation of why it\'s<br /><br />\n\'over the top\'.',0,1,1,0,0,0,'2008-03-17 20:27:28'),(46,'e31cc7c314d3f4d1e419cf059c3aab39',59,143,'Questions for Collectors','Hi,<br /><br />\nThis is Deanna Dahlsad from CollectorsQuest.com (you may know me better as Pop Tart from<br /><br />\nKitschy-Kitschy-Coo.